    FILTER SEMANTICS
    ================
    The `<filter>status=Closed</filter>` element uses ServiceNow's
    encoded-query string format. The semantics are:

      - `status` is the field name on `x_casemgmt_case` (defined in
        ../dictionary/x_casemgmt_case_status.xml).
      - `=` is the encoded-query equality operator.
      - `Closed` is the Choice label literal as defined in
        ../choices/sys_choice_case_status.xml. The Title Case spelling
        ("Closed" - NOT "CLOSED" or "closed" or "CLOSE") MUST match
        the Choice list verbatim per AAP Section 0.1.2 (which preserves
        the AAP's Title Case Choice convention from Section 0.5.7
        "Data-Model Mapping").
      - The encoded-query string contains no special XML characters
        (=, alphabetic chars only) and requires no XML escaping.

    Why filter to Closed only:
      1) Cases in any non-Closed status have NULL closed_date by
         dictionary definition (../dictionary/x_casemgmt_case_closed_date.xml
         documents that closed_date is mandatory=false and is set ONLY
         on the Resolved -> Closed transition by
         ../business_rules/x_casemgmt_set_closed_date.xml). Aggregating
         over NULL durations either returns NULL (if the calculated
         field handles NULL coalescence) or coerces to 0 (the
         calculated-field calculation script returns 0 for non-Closed
         cases) - both corrupt the average.
      2) The semantic intent of "average time to close" is the average
         over the population of cases that HAVE BEEN CLOSED. Cases in
         Draft / Open / In Progress / Pending / Resolved are NOT YET
         CLOSED by definition; including them in the denominator would
         drag the average toward zero by treating
         not-yet-closed-but-eventually-will-close cases as instant
         closures.

    AGGREGATION SEMANTICS
    =====================
    The combination of `<aggregate>AVG</aggregate>`, an
    `<aggregation_source>duration_to_close</aggregation_source>` that
    references the Function Field, and `<type>single_score</type>`
    produces a Duration-typed AVG. The SQL-equivalent GlideAggregate
    query the platform issues at dashboard-render time is:

        SELECT AVG(datediff(closed_date, opened_date))
        FROM   x_casemgmt_case
        WHERE  status = 'Closed'

    yielding a single Duration value that the dashboard widget
    renders as a human-readable interval (e.g., "5 Days 03:42:11").

    Behavior on edge cases:
      - Cases at non-Closed status have NULL `closed_date` (the
        column is set only on the Resolved -> Closed transition by
        ../business_rules/x_casemgmt_set_closed_date.xml). The filter
        `status=Closed` excludes those rows from the aggregate.
      - If the seed-data layer is missing closed_date timestamps on
        a Closed case, the function field returns NULL for that row
        and that row is excluded from the AVG (NULL durations are
        not averaged in). The widget still renders a real number
        for the remaining rows.
      - If zero rows satisfy the filter (e.g., on a fresh PDI before
        any Closed seed data is loaded), the platform renders the
        widget's empty-state placeholder. After the seed-data
        Update Set segment loads, the AVG renders the mean across
        the loaded Closed cases.

    DASHBOARD CONSUMPTION
    =====================
    The Manager View dashboard widget (in
    ../dashboards/pa_dashboards_x_casemgmt_manager_view.xml) references
    THIS record by `name`:
      <widget>
        <report_name>x_casemgmt_avg_time_to_close</report_name>
        ...
      </widget>
    NO sys_id reference - per AAP Section 0.7.2 "No-hardcoded-sys_id
    constraint" verbatim. The dashboard renders the single-score widget
    using the platform's native single-score-tile component.

    SEED DATA EXPECTATIONS
    ======================
    Under the Function Field implementation, the widget renders a
    real Duration AVG that is sensitive to the `opened_date` and
    `closed_date` values on the Closed demo cases. Per AAP Section
    0.4.1 directory enumeration, the 10 demo cases include:
      x_casemgmt_case_demo_06.xml (Closed, General Inquiry)
      x_casemgmt_case_demo_10.xml (Closed, Complaint)
    Seed-data authors MUST set realistic timestamps on these records
    so the widget renders a meaningful demo value. Recommended
    minimum: each Closed seed case should have
    `closed_date - opened_date` greater than zero (e.g., opened
    10 days ago, closed 3 days ago — a 7-day duration). With both
    Closed seeds populated to similar durations, the AVG is the
    arithmetic mean of the two case durations. With one Closed seed
    populated and the other left as opened-only, the AVG renders
    the populated case's duration. With neither populated, the
    widget renders the platform's empty-state placeholder until at
    least one Closed seed case has both timestamps set.

